<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is raised in the calibration step: "CyclicPaperStep" which is part of SDS 21-6-003 "Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]", when "Media Transport" is selected.
</p></section><section id="GUID-A33A3DD0-FCE3-4623-A147-ADB28AAF6B4F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Analyse/Repair</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the X-tran drive assembly is mounted and assembled correctly: 
<xref href="GUID-E4DCD77D-00F4-4BC3-8818-171A4187736D.xml" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>15 How to remove the Xtran drive assembly</xref>
</p></section><section id="GUID-104989D5-EE8E-4E21-AD66-8147F603C0C8" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">-
</p></section><section id="GUID-223EEC4A-98A5-4483-80CB-941AC774F6E1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">During this calibration step the uniformity of the X-tran drive roller is determined. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration prevents a specific pattern in the print quality (banding every 11 cm). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration step can fail when too many nozzles are failing in one of the black printheads or the media is not transported correctly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However, as this calibration step is proceeded by other steps is more likely the media transport is not working well.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-12A22F29-4989-4601-A883-7BC951F448D2.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
